 "text": "On 13.2 for /bin/sleep I see:\n\n  PID              START                END PRT  RES PRES REF SHD FLAG  TP PATH\n 1120     0x2a57e7f66000     0x2a57e7f67000 r--    1    2   3   1 CN--- vn /bin/sleep\n 1120     0x2a57e7f67000     0x2a57e7f69000 r-x    2    2   3   1 CN--- vn /bin/sleep\n 1120     0x2a57e7f69000     0x2a57e7f6a000 rw-    1    0   1   0 C---- vn /bin/sleep\n 1120     0x2a57e7f6a000     0x2a57e7f6b000 rw-    1    1   1   0 ----- df \n 1120     0x2a5fe86e6000     0x2a60086c6000 ---    0    0   0   0 ----- gd \n...\n\nphdrs:\n  LOAD           0x0000000000000000 0x0000000000000000 0x0000000000000000\n                 0x0000000000000bac 0x0000000000000bac  R      0x1000\n  LOAD           0x0000000000000bb0 0x0000000000001bb0 0x0000000000001bb0\n                 0x0000000000000820 0x0000000000000820  R E    0x1000\n  LOAD           0x00000000000013d0 0x00000000000033d0 0x00000000000033d0\n                 0x00000000000001f8 0x00000000000001f8  RW     0x1000\n  LOAD           0x00000000000015c8 0x00000000000045c8 0x00000000000045c8\n                 0x00000000000000c0 0x00000000000000d0  RW     0x1000\n\nSo it seems that we have all but the last PT_LOAD in each case, it's just that 13.2 has four PT_LOAD segments (R, RX, RW, RW) and we see 3 in procstat while 14.0 has three segments (R, RX, RW) and we see 2."
